d et al. 2002, p. 106.\n\n^ Holley, Donald (Autumn 2005). \"Leaving the Land of Opportunity: Arkansas and the Great Migration\". Arkansas Historical Quarterly. 64 (3): 247â€“248. doi:10.2307/40028047. JSTOR 40028047.\n\n^ \"Resident Population Data\". United States Census Bureau. Archived from the original on December 20, 2012. Retrieved July 4, 2012.\n\n^ \"Arkansas QuickFacts\". United States Census Bureau. June 7, 2012. Archived from the original on January 4, 2011. Retrieved July 4, 2012.\n\n^ \"Arkansas 2000 Census Population Center\". NOAA. Retrieved July 4, 2012.\n\n^ \"Archived copy\". Archived from the original on March 14, 2023. Retrieved March 11, 2023.{{cite web}}:  CS1 maint: archived copy as title (link)\n\n^ \"The 2022 Annual Homelessness Assessment Report (AHAR) to Congress\" (PDF). Huduser.gov. Retrieved September 30, 2023.\n\n^ \"Annual Estimates of the Resident Population for Counties: April 1, 2020 to July 1, 2023\". United States Census Bureau. Retrieved March 30, 2024.\n\n^ \"Historical Population Change Data (1910-2020)\". Census.gov. Archived from the original on April 29, 2021. Retrieved September 30, 2023.\n\n^ \"2019 Census Data for Races and Ethnicities\". data.census.gov. Retrieved June 3, 2021.\n\n^ \"Arkansas QuickFacts\". U.S. Census Bureau. Archived from the original on January 4, 2011. Retrieved December 13, 2004.\n\n^ Exner, Rich (June 3, 2012). \"Americans under age 1 now mostly minorities, but not in Ohio: Statistical Snapshot\". The Plain Dealer.\n\n^ \"Race and Ethnicity in the United States: 2010 Census and 2020 Census\". census.gov. United States Census Bureau. August 12, 2021. Retrieved September 26, 2021.\n\n^ \"Historical Census Statistics on Population Totals By Race, 1790 to 1990, and By Hispanic Origin, 1970 to 1990, For The United States, Regions, Divisions, and States\". Archived from the original on July 25, 2008. Retrieved April 17, 2021.\n\n^ \"Population of Arkansasâ€”Census 2010 and 2000 Interactive Map, Demograp